PN,39801
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1774905063
OL,3,CTumour mutation mapping could boost
OL,4,Ctargeted cancer therapies
OL,6,FMore people could benefit from
OL,7,Ftargeted therapies for breast or
OL,8,Fovarian cancer, experts have said
OL,9,Fafter conducting mapping mutations in
OL,10,Ftumours.
OL,12,FScientists from the Manchester Cancer
OL,13,FResearch Centre and the Institute of
OL,14,FCancer Research have for the first
OL,15,Ftime decoded the full range of
OL,16,Fmutations that drive tumour growth.
OL,18,FTheir findings could pave the way for
OL,19,Fa new era in precision medicine,
OL,20,Foffering more effective treatments for
OL,21,Fthousands of people with cancer.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1774905063
OL,3,CTumour mutation mapping could boost
OL,4,Ctargeted cancer therapies
OL,6,FThey could also unlock the reason
OL,7,Fbehind a rise in bowel cancer among
OL,8,Fyounger adults. Over six years, a team
OL,9,Fof scientists forensically examined
OL,10,Fthe genetic make-up of tumours in 16
OL,11,Fdifferent cancers.
OL,13,FThey examined an "enormous" amount of
OL,14,Fdata from 10,983 cancer patients
OL,15,Ftaking part in the 100,000 Genomes
OL,16,FProject.
OL,26,@uD@ROUuD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1774905063
OL,3,CTumour mutation mapping could boost
OL,4,Ctargeted cancer therapies
OL,6,FUsing whole-genome sequencing, the
OL,7,Fresearch team catalogued 370 million
OL,8,Fmutations and assigned them to 134
OL,9,Fdistinct mutational "signatures" `
OL,10,Fpatterns of DNA damage that act like
OL,11,Ffingerprints of the processes that
OL,12,Fcaused the cancer.
OL,14,FOf these, 26 signatures were
OL,15,Fidentified which were not previously
OL,16,Fincluded in the database of known
OL,17,Fsignatures used by many scientists `
OL,18,Fthe Catalogue of Somatic Mutations in
OL,19,FCancer (Cosmic) ` according to the
OL,20,Fstudy published in the journal Nature
OL,21,FGenetics.
OL,26,@qD@UOUqD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1774905063
OL,3,CTumour mutation mapping could boost
OL,4,Ctargeted cancer therapies
OL,6,FThe researchers said the findings
OL,7,Findicate many more patients may
OL,8,Fbenefit from precision therapies.
OL,10,FThe study identified a large number of
OL,11,Ftumours with evidence of homologous
OL,12,Frecombination deficiency (HRD) - a
OL,13,Fweakness in DNA repair that makes
OL,14,Fcancers vulnerable to targeted cancer
OL,15,Fdrugs PARP inhibitors and platinum-
OL,16,Fbased chemotherapy.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1774905063
OL,3,CTumour mutation mapping could boost
OL,4,Ctargeted cancer therapies
OL,6,FIt said HRD was identified in 16% of
OL,7,Fbreast cancer tumours and 14% of
OL,8,Fovarian cancer tumours, so based on UK
OL,9,Ffigures, researchers estimated more
OL,10,Fthan 7,700 breast cancer patients and
OL,11,F1,000 ovarian cancer patients could
OL,12,Fbenefit from HRD-targeted therapies `
OL,13,Fmuch more than currently identified
OL,14,Fthrough standard genetic testing for
OL,15,Fmutations in genes such as BRCA1/BRCA2
OL,16,Falone.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1774905063
OL,3,CTumour mutation mapping could boost
OL,4,Ctargeted cancer therapies
OL,6,FWhile the researchers stressed that
OL,7,Fclinical trials are needed to
OL,8,Fascertain that patients with HRD
OL,9,Fsignatures respond to PARP inhibitors,
OL,10,Fthe finding could lead to a
OL,11,Fsignificantly higher number of
OL,12,Fpatients benefitting from precision
OL,13,Fmedicine for cancer.
OL,15,FExperts said the study also lends
OL,16,Fsupport to a theory that toxins
OL,17,Fproduced by particular strains of E.
OL,18,Fcoli, a bacteria in the gut, could be
OL,19,Flinked to the rise in bowel cancer in
OL,20,Fyounger people.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1774905063
OL,3,CTumour mutation mapping could boost
OL,4,Ctargeted cancer therapies
OL,6,FMany strains of the bacteria are
OL,7,Fharmless to humans but others can make
OL,8,Fpeople sick with diarrhoea, urinary
OL,9,Ftract infections and pneumonia, among
OL,10,Fother illnesses.
OL,12,FThe team found this signature from
OL,13,Fthese toxins occurs more in younger
OL,14,Fpatients than older ones, in contrast
OL,15,Fwith several other signatures that
OL,16,Ftend to increase with a patient's age.
OL,18,FData from Cancer Research UK suggests
OL,19,Fone in 20 bowel cancers is diagnosed
OL,20,Fin people aged under 50.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1774905063
OL,3,CTumour mutation mapping could boost
OL,4,Ctargeted cancer therapies
OL,6,FFigures provided by the charity up to
OL,7,F2019 show a 52% increase in incidence
OL,8,Frates for adults aged 25 to 49 since
OL,9,Fthe early 1990s.
OL,11,FDavid Wedge, professor of cancer
OL,12,Fgenomics and data science at the
OL,13,FUniversity of Manchester, said: "Every
OL,14,Fcancer develops because DNA is damaged
OL,15,Fover time.
OL,17,F"Different causes such as ultraviolet
OL,18,Flight, tobacco smoke or inherited gene
OL,19,Ffaults leave different patterns in the
OL,20,Fgenome.
OL,26,@uD@aOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1774905063
OL,3,CTumour mutation mapping could boost
OL,4,Ctargeted cancer therapies
OL,6,F"By reading these patterns we can now
OL,7,Funderstand, in a larger proportion of
OL,8,Fcancers, what caused the cancer, when
OL,9,Fkey mutations occurred, and which
OL,10,Ftreatments are most likely to work.
OL,12,F"Until now, most testing has focused
OL,13,Fon mutations of a single base (or
OL,14,F'letter') in a cancer's DNA.
OL,16,F"By analysing the entire genome and
OL,17,Fexamining more complex mutations that
OL,18,Faffect multiple bases, I hope our
OL,19,Fresearch contributes to better
OL,20,Fpredictions of which treatment might
OL,21,Fbenefit specific patients.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1774905063
OL,3,CTumour mutation mapping could boost
OL,4,Ctargeted cancer therapies
OL,6,F"This could enable better targeting of
OL,7,Ftreatment to those patients most
OL,8,Flikely to benefit, given the genetic
OL,9,Fmake-up of their tumours."
OL,11,FProfessor Richard Houlston, from the
OL,12,FInstitute of Cancer Research, said:
OL,13,F"This study provides one of the
OL,14,Fclearest demonstrations yet that
OL,15,Freading the full genetic history of a
OL,16,Ftumour can unlock clues to better
OL,17,Fpatient care.
OL,19,F"The future of cancer treatment lies
OL,20,Fnot just in finding mutations, but in
OL,21,Funderstanding the story they tell."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@ZO]uD@AOU}D@cO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
